1
00:00:00,440 --> 00:00:01,480
This way, please.

2
00:00:02,800 --> 00:00:03,640
Lead the way.

3
00:00:17,700 --> 00:00:18,280
You there!

4
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:20,400
What goes on here?!

5
00:00:24,740 --> 00:00:26,680
I was tending to him with herbal remedies.

6
00:00:28,760 --> 00:00:30,040
His foot has been injured.

7
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:32,320
I fear it may become infected.

8
00:00:36,340 --> 00:00:37,600
All this is owing to Tan,

9
00:00:37,980 --> 00:00:39,200
who stepped on his foot

10
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:42,960
and caused you this trouble.

11
00:00:48,740 --> 00:00:49,440
Tan.

12
00:00:50,340 --> 00:00:52,160
You must take greater care.

13
00:00:53,040 --> 00:00:55,440
In performing Khon,
one must observe proper decorum.

14
00:00:56,680 --> 00:00:58,280
Do not complicate matters.

15
00:01:00,440 --> 00:01:02,760
I beg your pardon, Master.

16
00:01:14,060 --> 00:01:15,680
You played most foully.

17
00:01:17,820 --> 00:01:18,960
What is fair

18
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:20,560
or foul

19
00:01:21,520 --> 00:01:23,320
is a matter of opinion!

20
00:01:24,360 --> 00:01:26,800
Tan, Saen, enough.

21
00:01:27,840 --> 00:01:29,600
Performing Khon for the Department

22
00:01:29,820 --> 00:01:32,080
is more important
than this petty matter, is it not?

23
00:01:34,780 --> 00:01:36,960
Let us each go our way and take a rest.

24
00:01:42,080 --> 00:01:42,760
Tan,

25
00:01:43,960 --> 00:01:45,040
follow me.

26
00:01:58,100 --> 00:01:59,960
We should take greater care.

27
00:02:11,820 --> 00:02:16,020
[Tanakorn Chuen-arom as Saen/Sand]

28
00:02:16,220 --> 00:02:20,780
[Wacharathon Wongyai as Rak/Lucky]

29
00:02:21,100 --> 00:02:24,900
[Worachai Areewong as Tan/Thank]

30
00:02:25,260 --> 00:02:29,980
[Khitaphat Choothai as Chim/Charm]

31
00:02:30,180 --> 00:02:33,580
[Kornkamon Supaseripap as Vila/ViVi]

32
00:02:33,860 --> 00:02:37,840
[Rungtiva Sangngoen as Prink
Napat Seela as Rit/Ton]

33
00:02:38,020 --> 00:02:41,420
[Chalisa Schaub as Kamala
Weeraachai Hatgovit as Phraya Banleng]

34
00:02:41,580 --> 00:02:45,780
[Nithiroj Simakamtorn as Phraya Dechanarong
Rattanachai Phakdirat as Khon Master]

35
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:02,400
Why did you trouble the Royal Master?

36
00:03:03,100 --> 00:03:04,180
What are you plotting?

37
00:03:08,160 --> 00:03:10,160
I merely served as his eyes and ears.

38
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:12,920
What is wrong with that?

39
00:03:14,480 --> 00:03:16,280
For whose sake was it truly done?

40
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:18,280
Was it for the Royal Master,

41
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:19,720
for the school,

42
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:21,160
or for whom?

43
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:24,560
For no one.

44
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:26,960
If it be for anyone,

45
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:29,080
it must be for me.

46
00:03:31,160 --> 00:03:34,640
I long to see
the faces of those false nobles unmasked.

47
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:37,320
Though of noble birth,

48
00:03:37,960 --> 00:03:39,240
they are yet crude.

49
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:41,090
They are equally foul.

50
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:42,000
Enough, Tan.

51
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:45,480
You may seek your vengeance,

52
00:03:46,480 --> 00:03:48,280
yet you drag another into the pit with you.

53
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:50,760
Give it thought.

54
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:53,360
What has Saen done wrong?

55
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:56,440
He has been helping you
since the first day.

56
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:00,600
And you

57
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:03,480
are fond of him.

58
00:04:04,980 --> 00:04:08,000
Why does Saen
never lay blame upon that graceful Rak?!

59
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:10,440
If he had never been,

60
00:04:10,940 --> 00:04:12,800
Saen and I
would not have to suffer like this.

61
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:15,720
Blame no one.

62
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:18,040
Jealousy

63
00:04:18,580 --> 00:04:20,080
can burn you whole.

64
00:04:21,040 --> 00:04:21,920
Do you know it?

65
00:04:25,740 --> 00:04:27,560
Let it burn me whole!

66
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:29,720
At least

67
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:32,600
I may witness their suffering as well.

68
00:04:58,680 --> 00:04:59,560
I suppose

69
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:01,920
we ought to train separately.

70
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:04,080
Our roles are sworn enemies.

71
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:07,920
I fear what others may say.

72
00:05:10,760 --> 00:05:11,440
Very well.

73
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:14,040
I am an obstacle to you, am I not?

74
00:05:22,760 --> 00:05:23,680
By no means, Master.

75
00:05:27,540 --> 00:05:28,640
I understand.

76
00:05:30,100 --> 00:05:31,690
Then I shall attend to my own training.

77
00:06:12,300 --> 00:06:13,400
What are the two of you doing?

78
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:17,600
I shall inform the Royal Master.

79
00:06:19,260 --> 00:06:20,500
Your dance movements

80
00:06:21,440 --> 00:06:22,880
ill suit your roles.

81
00:06:24,640 --> 00:06:25,740
What shall you inform him of?

82
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:29,040
Khon dancers

83
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,500
must train in their art, must they not?

84
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:36,360
He is right, Tan.

85
00:06:38,020 --> 00:06:39,400
They dance just as the text says.

86
00:06:41,280 --> 00:06:43,000
Think no ill of them.

87
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:46,640
I saw it with my own eyes.

88
00:06:47,390 --> 00:06:48,800
Such movements

89
00:06:49,420 --> 00:06:50,760
are found nowhere in the text.

90
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:54,040
Will you side with them once more, Chim?

91
00:06:55,340 --> 00:06:56,800
I speak what I see.

92
00:06:57,340 --> 00:06:58,880
I side with none.

93
00:07:10,440 --> 00:07:11,200
Rak.

94
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:22,360
You dance with grace, Rak.

95
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:24,800
Next Saturday,

96
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:26,800
my house shall play host to an event.

97
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:29,420
I would have you accompany me.

98
00:07:30,320 --> 00:07:31,080
As you wish.

99
00:07:32,040 --> 00:07:33,320
I shall go without fail.

100
00:08:05,620 --> 00:08:06,440
Okay.

101
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:08,520
Why don't we discuss

102
00:08:09,080 --> 00:08:12,000
how we'd save this club

103
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:15,420
without resorting to bickering
and fighting like before?

104
00:08:15,980 --> 00:08:17,200
I didn't do that.

105
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,940
I was just showing
the Thotsakan energy within me.

106
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:22,960
Fierce. Unafraid of anyone.

107
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:26,320
You call that showing?

108
00:08:27,280 --> 00:08:28,730
More like ruining.

109
00:08:28,760 --> 00:08:30,480
Ugh, enough already.

110
00:08:31,200 --> 00:08:33,440
Stop bringing it up.

111
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:39,680
Our club
is going to be suspended soon, right?

112
00:08:41,680 --> 00:08:43,080
If you keep fighting,

113
00:08:43,300 --> 00:08:45,480
the club will really be disbanded.

114
00:08:46,760 --> 00:08:48,080
I wasn't fighting.

115
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:51,080
I just don't wanna work with a dinosaur

116
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:53,000
who listens to nobody.

117
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:57,480
I also don't wanna work with someone
who treats Khon like a toy.

118
00:09:02,300 --> 00:09:04,240
Hi, guys.

119
00:09:04,780 --> 00:09:06,050
It's me, ViVi.

120
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:08,040
I'm ready to be your Sida.

121
00:09:10,920 --> 00:09:11,680
Who is this?

122
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:26,240
This is ViVi.

123
00:09:26,520 --> 00:09:27,520
My close friend.

124
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:31,280
I was thinking of having her play Sida.

125
00:09:32,060 --> 00:09:33,280
She just got back from abroad.

126
00:09:34,580 --> 00:09:36,960
But soon
we won't have a club for Sida anymore.

127
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:39,960
Because of the scandal?

128
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:43,000
Yeah...

129
00:09:49,880 --> 00:09:51,640
Okay, then.

130
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:53,880
So, which direction are we going?

131
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:55,760
The new direction.

132
00:09:57,260 --> 00:09:59,000
Innovative Khon,

133
00:09:59,460 --> 00:10:00,680
designed to connect with young people.

134
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:04,320
There'll be lights, sounds,
flair, AI, and special effects.

135
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,160
That's a circus,

136
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:07,520
not Khon.

137
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:10,200
What about you, then?

138
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:12,640
Traditional Khon,

139
00:10:12,940 --> 00:10:14,400
as taught by Khon Masters.

140
00:10:14,860 --> 00:10:16,360
Khon exists because of its roots,

141
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:18,000
not because of viral videos.

142
00:10:18,320 --> 00:10:19,280
"Roots."

143
00:10:19,780 --> 00:10:21,360
Then...

144
00:10:22,900 --> 00:10:24,200
Why don't we combine them?

145
00:10:25,240 --> 00:10:26,080
What do you think?

146
00:10:28,980 --> 00:10:31,320
Will the principal approve that?

147
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:33,520
I'm making a call now.

148
00:10:34,180 --> 00:10:35,440
A call?

149
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:36,400
Who's it to?

150
00:10:36,760 --> 00:10:37,720
Hi, Uncle.

151
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:40,720
I have a project
with the idea of a contemporary Ramakien.

152
00:10:40,900 --> 00:10:43,530
We'll combine the roots of Khon,

153
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:44,880
which is Lucky's idea,

154
00:10:45,020 --> 00:10:47,240
with Sand's creativity

155
00:10:47,270 --> 00:10:49,680
to create something accessible to everyone.

156
00:10:50,120 --> 00:10:51,360
Okay, Uncle.

157
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:52,680
Thank you so much.

158
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:56,160
Okay.

159
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:57,480
My uncle approves.

160
00:10:57,540 --> 00:10:59,000
Huh? Uncle?

161
00:11:00,320 --> 00:11:02,880
Why are we getting approval from your uncle
instead of the principal?

162
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:05,440
That's because ViVi's uncle

163
00:11:05,660 --> 00:11:08,960
is the man we talked to earlier.

164
00:11:10,360 --> 00:11:11,600
Earlier...

165
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:13,160
The principal...

166
00:11:13,900 --> 00:11:14,760
Deal?

167
00:11:16,980 --> 00:11:17,720
Deal.

168
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:20,760
Deal.

169
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:24,040
Hey!

170
00:11:29,860 --> 00:11:31,040
Raise your arm higher.

171
00:11:34,120 --> 00:11:36,440
Yes, sir, Khon Master of all.

172
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:43,880
Lower.

173
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:52,000
Tilt your head and bow slightly.

174
00:11:52,740 --> 00:11:53,720
Stay still.

175
00:12:01,260 --> 00:12:02,240
What are you on now?

176
00:12:03,740 --> 00:12:05,400
This is not Tokusatsu.

177
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:07,400
This is Khon.

178
00:12:07,980 --> 00:12:09,720
It has its own structures and conventions.

179
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:11,680
What?

180
00:12:13,320 --> 00:12:14,640
Didn't we agree

181
00:12:15,080 --> 00:12:17,760
to combine the two ideas?

182
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:20,840
To make it happen,

183
00:12:21,060 --> 00:12:22,400
you first need to know the roots

184
00:12:22,680 --> 00:12:24,000
so you can build on them.

185
00:12:24,340 --> 00:12:25,920
If you don't know the conventions,

186
00:12:26,280 --> 00:12:27,680
how can you take it to the next level?

187
00:12:34,340 --> 00:12:35,240
I'm tired.

188
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:37,520
Can I have a 3-minute break?

189
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:42,080
Thotsakan takes 3 minutes to recharge.

190
00:12:46,340 --> 00:12:47,760
You call yourself Thotsakan,

191
00:12:48,440 --> 00:12:51,680
but you have no idea
what Thotsakan's heart really is.

192
00:12:52,160 --> 00:12:52,760
What?

193
00:12:53,240 --> 00:12:55,840
Then hurry up and teach me already.

194
00:12:56,700 --> 00:12:57,680
Uh...

195
00:12:58,220 --> 00:12:59,840
I think you two should take a break.

196
00:13:00,250 --> 00:13:01,880
You seem tense.

197
00:13:01,940 --> 00:13:03,440
Yeah, right.

198
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:06,250
Let's take a break before we continue.

199
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:07,370
You'll feel more relaxed.

200
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:08,360
No!

201
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:10,960
If you don't get the basics,

202
00:13:11,640 --> 00:13:12,730
teaching you is pointless.

203
00:13:12,760 --> 00:13:13,640
Alright, man.

204
00:13:14,400 --> 00:13:16,080
Your Khon is like learning math.

205
00:13:16,380 --> 00:13:18,320
Does it have to follow
the formula precisely?

206
00:13:18,560 --> 00:13:19,650
I must get a zero, then.

207
00:13:19,680 --> 00:13:21,280
You have no right to talk about Khon!

208
00:13:22,320 --> 00:13:24,240
You don't even know
what the right rhythm is!

209
00:13:26,480 --> 00:13:27,960
I'll create my own rhythm

210
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:29,890
because your Khon

211
00:13:29,920 --> 00:13:31,840
- is too slow for this world!
- Cut it out, Sand!

212
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:33,850
That's enough.

213
00:13:33,880 --> 00:13:34,720
Don't traditions

214
00:13:35,040 --> 00:13:36,320
need room to breathe?

215
00:13:37,480 --> 00:13:39,050
Would you rather
see them rotting in museums?

216
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:40,880
But what you call innovation

217
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:43,520
is no different from destruction.

218
00:13:50,400 --> 00:13:51,040
Right.

219
00:13:51,520 --> 00:13:53,240
If I'm such a problem to you,

220
00:13:53,550 --> 00:13:55,630
then I quit! Enough of this sh*t!

221
00:13:55,660 --> 00:13:56,800
- Sand!
- Sand!

222
00:13:57,160 --> 00:13:58,520
- Sand!
- Good!

223
00:13:59,080 --> 00:13:59,720
Leave!

224
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:01,480
Lucky!

225
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:05,400
Why would you say that?

226
00:14:15,520 --> 00:14:17,270
[So cool! This is what modern Khon is about]

227
00:14:17,300 --> 00:14:19,050
[I want to learn Khon now]

228
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:20,830
[Good energy, Thai hero vibes]

229
00:14:22,240 --> 00:14:25,000
[I get that it's meant for young folks,

230
00:14:25,020 --> 00:14:27,780
but it's still
disrespectful to the original art form]

231
00:14:28,880 --> 00:14:30,560
You call yourself Thotsakan,

232
00:14:31,740 --> 00:14:32,920
but you have no idea

233
00:14:33,720 --> 00:14:35,680
what Thotsakan's heart really is.

234
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:46,290
[Why is the club president
so against new ideas?]

235
00:14:46,320 --> 00:14:49,280
[Khon will go extinct
because of these dinosaurs]

236
00:14:54,680 --> 00:14:56,760
Don't traditions need room to breathe

237
00:14:57,280 --> 00:14:59,000
instead of rotting away in museums?

238
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:30,600
Sizzling, sizzling, sizzling.

239
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:33,840
- Looks delicious.
- Looks good.

240
00:15:34,120 --> 00:15:34,920
Guys,

241
00:15:35,520 --> 00:15:36,880
I invited Sand.

242
00:15:37,040 --> 00:15:38,840
He thinks he'll just come here for dinner.

243
00:15:39,080 --> 00:15:40,440
He doesn't know about Lucky.

244
00:15:40,640 --> 00:15:43,000
Perfect. I invited Lucky here.

245
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:45,600
Okay. So tonight's plan is...

246
00:15:45,880 --> 00:15:47,400
not letting any of them leave this table

247
00:15:47,800 --> 00:15:48,920
until they're on good terms.

248
00:15:49,640 --> 00:15:50,200
Okay?

249
00:15:55,400 --> 00:15:56,240
Are they almost here?

250
00:15:56,720 --> 00:15:57,560
I don't know.

251
00:15:58,400 --> 00:16:00,720
Almost ready. Sizzling, sizzling.

252
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:02,400
Lucky, here!

253
00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:04,880
- What's up?
- Are you hungry?

254
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:05,760
Of course.

255
00:16:06,920 --> 00:16:07,840
Looks delicious.

256
00:16:07,840 --> 00:16:08,880
Hey, Sand!

257
00:16:09,480 --> 00:16:10,360
Come sit here.

258
00:16:10,840 --> 00:16:12,280
Hurry, before it burns.

259
00:16:20,120 --> 00:16:21,040
Here you go.

260
00:16:21,400 --> 00:16:23,720
Ice-cold Coke for you.

261
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:25,000
Thanks.

262
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:27,440
Look at this.

263
00:16:28,160 --> 00:16:29,520
Our rival school

264
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:33,520
has this handsome guy
who plays Khon on TV.

265
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:34,840
Wow...

266
00:16:35,080 --> 00:16:36,600
They're already way ahead.

267
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:40,160
It won't be long until
people forget about our club.

268
00:16:41,160 --> 00:16:43,680
But now we have a mutual enemy.

269
00:16:44,280 --> 00:16:45,600
No more fighting each other

270
00:16:45,720 --> 00:16:48,400
because those guys stole our stage.

271
00:16:51,320 --> 00:16:52,600
We have to get our stage back.

272
00:16:55,320 --> 00:16:56,120
Exactly.

273
00:16:57,080 --> 00:16:58,120
But this time

274
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:00,920
we must live up to our reputation.

275
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:06,280
See?

276
00:17:06,360 --> 00:17:09,000
You two are finally on the same page.

277
00:17:11,480 --> 00:17:12,480
It might work.

278
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:16,560
Yeah.

279
00:17:17,720 --> 00:17:19,040
But you have to listen to me more.

280
00:17:21,560 --> 00:17:22,280
Mhm.

281
00:17:23,280 --> 00:17:24,160
Perfect.
Well...

282
00:17:25,560 --> 00:17:27,360
What should we call our new project?

283
00:17:36,440 --> 00:17:37,600
Vertical Ram.

284
00:17:38,280 --> 00:17:40,880
A vertical version of the Ramakien.

285
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:43,960
- Wow.
- Sounds cool.

286
00:17:46,240 --> 00:17:47,720
- Wow...
- That sounds cool.

287
00:17:47,960 --> 00:17:50,120
Yeah, let's go with that.
Sounds pretty cool.

288
00:17:54,160 --> 00:17:55,000
Cheers.

289
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:56,400
To Vertical Ram.

290
00:17:57,040 --> 00:17:59,480
And to the Khon who refuses to die.

291
00:18:00,840 --> 00:18:02,760
Woohoo!!

292
00:18:04,920 --> 00:18:06,320
Watch out for spills!

293
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:16,560
Good morning, Uncle.

294
00:18:16,720 --> 00:18:18,040
Good morning, Rak.

295
00:18:18,640 --> 00:18:20,600
You are here at last.
Come in, and sit with me.

296
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:30,200
Is your daughter Vila...

297
00:18:30,680 --> 00:18:32,600
I do not know when...

298
00:18:37,840 --> 00:18:40,320
A very good morning to you, Phraya.

299
00:18:42,160 --> 00:18:44,600
Why, it has been ages
since we last met, Vila.

300
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:46,960
No need for titles.

301
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:48,000
Call me Uncle.

302
00:18:48,400 --> 00:18:49,800
We are no strangers to each other.

303
00:18:51,240 --> 00:18:53,920
A very good morning to you, Uncle.

304
00:18:56,720 --> 00:18:58,640
This is Rak,

305
00:18:59,080 --> 00:19:01,160
my youngest son.

306
00:19:04,200 --> 00:19:05,600
He plays Rama.

307
00:19:06,480 --> 00:19:07,800
He is known to all.

308
00:19:14,040 --> 00:19:15,000
Well...

309
00:19:15,160 --> 00:19:16,680
Give him your greeting.

310
00:19:16,880 --> 00:19:17,960
Be not bashful.

311
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:22,040
Good morning, Mister Rak.

312
00:19:25,360 --> 00:19:26,840
Good day to you as well.

313
00:19:28,320 --> 00:19:29,680
Very well, Vila.

314
00:19:30,680 --> 00:19:32,840
Invite Rak to take a stroll about the house.

315
00:19:33,520 --> 00:19:36,560
Why, what a splendid idea that is.

316
00:19:36,600 --> 00:19:39,680
We talk of matters most dull.

317
00:19:40,760 --> 00:19:41,560
Pardon me...

318
00:19:42,440 --> 00:19:43,480
I wish not to trouble her.

319
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:45,760
I am well content here.

320
00:19:48,160 --> 00:19:49,480
Do not object.

321
00:19:50,600 --> 00:19:52,400
Think of it as honoring the host.

322
00:19:55,360 --> 00:19:56,080
As you wish.

323
00:19:58,400 --> 00:19:59,560
Very well...

324
00:20:00,080 --> 00:20:02,360
May I lead the way?

325
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:06,240
By all means, Vila.

326
00:20:27,440 --> 00:20:30,320
The weather is fair today, Mister Rak.

327
00:20:33,520 --> 00:20:35,480
You may call me Rak, Vila.

328
00:20:36,640 --> 00:20:37,960
Would it be proper?

329
00:20:38,920 --> 00:20:40,280
Most certainly.

330
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:42,160
My father

331
00:20:42,200 --> 00:20:44,600
and your father are friends.

332
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:46,360
We are no strangers.

333
00:20:46,840 --> 00:20:48,600
No need for titles.

334
00:20:50,560 --> 00:20:53,360
What age are you, Rak?

335
00:20:54,280 --> 00:20:55,120
Twenty.

336
00:20:55,720 --> 00:20:56,880
What of yourself?

337
00:20:57,400 --> 00:20:58,800
I am eighteen.

338
00:21:00,520 --> 00:21:01,480
See?

339
00:21:01,880 --> 00:21:03,280
We are near in age.

340
00:21:05,440 --> 00:21:07,600
You need not call me by the title.

341
00:21:10,120 --> 00:21:11,640
Rak,

342
00:21:12,720 --> 00:21:14,440
your Khon performance

343
00:21:14,760 --> 00:21:16,160
is most graceful.

344
00:21:16,720 --> 00:21:18,680
I wish to be Sida

345
00:21:18,880 --> 00:21:20,480
in place of one of the gentlemen.

346
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:23,040
If I may ask,

347
00:21:23,360 --> 00:21:25,880
could you teach me to dance?

348
00:21:40,080 --> 00:21:41,440
Let that be for another day, Vila.

349
00:21:41,960 --> 00:21:43,360
I have matters to attend to today.
